BFN 

  [Text] Sri Lanka will sign a science and technology 
agreement with South Korea. Prime Minister Ranil Wickremasinghe 
left for South Korea on an official visit last night. He will 
sign an agreement with his counterpart Yi Yong-tok [name as 
heard]. The prime minister is also expected to hold talks with 
potential investors and industrialists. High-level officials of 
major Korean industries are expected to meet Mr. Wickremasinghe. 
He is scheduled to tour industrial zones in the country. South 
Korean cooperation will be sought to establish technical 
training institutes and to train our youths in that country. 
Leading local businessmen are simultaneously visiting South 
Korea to hold discussions on prospective investments and trade 
promotion. 

